AB  - Background: Today's nursing students will always face the health effects of climate change in the coming years. Methods: This research was carried out with students (N=148) between 1-May 2021 - 1 June 2021 and no sample selection was made. As a data collection form, a questionnaire containing the descriptive characteristics of the students and a questionnaire on climate change developed by the researchers were used. Results: 19.6% of the students gave the answer of university education as a climate change information source. Students stated that they could take effective actions towards the effects of climate change on health (p=0.038) and that they should be well prepared for the effects of climate change on health (p=0.032). Conclusions: Although nursing students have embraced their role in responding to climate change, they think that they are not adequately prepared at school.
